Semantic Html 

1.<header>  is a semantic HTML5 tag used to define the section of a webpage 
2.<nav> defines a section containing navigation links.
3. <main> Contains the main content of the webpage. 
4.<section> Groups related content under a common heading.
5.<article> Represents independent, self-contained content such as news article or product description.
6.<table> displays data in rows and colums
7.<form>Collects user input.
8.<footer> Defines the footer of a webpage or section . contains copyright information, contact details links.
